Product description

A NEW CONCEPT FOR LIGHT SWITCH

Make Your Life Simple

The illuminated light switch was developed by our senior engineer Nick, there are times his family are going to need to be up and about during the wee hours-and nightlight can help keep them safe, at the same time he hope the night light wont dangerous for his children and helps them sleep.

The illuminated light switch was designed for a truly simple, safe solution to the household nightlight.Now we would like to share this product with every home.

With Light sensing technology, SOZULAMP illuminated 3 way light switch is the perfect addition to your home lighting. Softly led lights are a good night light for anyone to prevent tripping on anything; Don't need to turn on the ceiling light and hurt your eyes at midnight; just the right amount of light that doesn't interfere with sleep; Easy to locate the switch in the dark, and freeing up an outlet. your home will be safer and enhanced with the addition of the illuminated light switch.

Frequently Asked Questions

  1. What are illuminated switches?------An illuminated light switch lights up from the row of leds on the bottom edge of the light switch when the load is turned OFF, good night light for anyone or easy location in a dark room.
  2. How does it work?------The LED illuminated wall switch has an internal circuit that provides just enough electricity to power the LED night lights(lighting loads without ghosting or flickering), and this circuit becomes active only when the switch is off.
  3. What is ghosting?------Ghosting is when lighting loads can faintly glow even when the light switch is off. This is caused by electricity to power the LED night lights and is a common problem seen with illuminated switches.
  4. How to eliminate ghosting?------Please use greater than 9 wattage lighting loads.
  5. Does it have a direction?------No! LED light bar on the top and bottom sides of the illuminated switch .
  6. Does it need a neutral?------No! The LED illuminated switch does not require a neutral to work.
  7. Does it need to be grounded?------No! But we recommend a ground wire on light switch.
  8. Can the LED automatic ON-OFF?------Yes! There is a small dot on the switch itself behind which there is a dusk to dawn sensor, it knows when to turn LEDs on/off automatically.
  9. Does it have a motion sensor?------No! There is no motion sensor.
  10. What are the types of it?------The LED illuminated light switch is available in standard Single Pole, 3-Way.
  11. What is the color of the LED?------Warm white(3000K) and Daylight white(6000K).
  12. Which loads are compatible?------The illuminated switches are designed for all types of bulbs and fixtures, including LED, CFL, Incandescent, etc.
  13. Does it including wallplates?------NO! Excluding wall plates.
  14. Is bright enough?------It provides a low light, but the light enough to find the switch and enough to navigate when your eyes are adapted to the darkness. if the LED illuminated switch does not provide your desired intensity, consider our LED night light outlet(please see related products below).

    I like the modern look it gives to my light switches and that it illuminates hunting fir a light switch in the dark. They also serve as a nightlight anywhere you use them. I like the daylight (blue light) versions, but you may want the warm light ones for bathrooms and bedrooms. Just as our smartphones blue light can trigger our body's natural water and sleep cycles, so can any blue light source. I don't really care one way or the other and I like the daylight versions ate brighter.

    I bought a couple if these to use on my basement stair light switches and my entry light switches. But I like how they look, (even with an accent color wall plate, instead of a matching white wall plate) that I ordered more for all my light switches.

    Just remember that you may need either the 3-way or single pole version depending on your light switch wiring. Any switch that has two locations for the same light fixture are 3-way. Single location would be the other single pole. They are easy to wire, provided: if you are mentally intelligent and competent to do so. If not or if any doubts, always hire a licensed electrician that is. Or someone else you know that is capable and competent to work on electricy. Unlike electrical reciticas, light switches can be wired several different ways. hus, mis wiring a light switch can cause electrical current to overload heat up and start a electrical fire. Saving a few dollars just to end up burning down your house, is never worth the risk.
